<div id="review_4271478919" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4271478919" />
    <a title="Veronique" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/12371602-veronique"><img alt="Veronique" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1590509341p2/12371602.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4271478919?book_show_action=true">Oct 09, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Veronique" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Veronique" href="/user/show/12371602-veronique">Veronique</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780199568840" href="/book/show/11325318-collected-ghost-stories">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/12371602-veronique?shelf=literary">literary</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/12371602-veronique?shelf=paranormal">paranormal</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/12371602-veronique?shelf=r2021">r2021</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/12371602-veronique?shelf=favourites">favourites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/12371602-veronique?shelf=short-story">short-story</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/12371602-veronique?shelf=classics">classics</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4271478919" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17383569762415732172">4.5* <br/><br/>When you mention ‘ghost stories’, M.R. James’s name is bound to appear in the conversation. His stories, especially his most famous one <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/22916811.Oh__Whistle__and_I_ll_Come_to_you__My_Lad' title='Oh, Whistle, and I&apos;ll Come to you, My Lad by M.R. James' rel='nofollow noopener'>Oh, Whistle, and I&apos;ll Come to you, My Lad</a>, are included in most anthologies of the genre. <br/><br/>Over the years, I have read quite a few of his, enjoying them immensely, before I finally bought this volume. Here I discovered more excellent tales but also so much more. The introduction to the author and his life was fascinating. I knew James was an academic but had</span>
  <span id="freeText17383569762415732172" style="display:none">4.5* <br /><br />When you mention ‘ghost stories’, M.R. James’s name is bound to appear in the conversation. His stories, especially his most famous one <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/22916811.Oh__Whistle__and_I_ll_Come_to_you__My_Lad" title="Oh, Whistle, and I'll Come to you, My Lad by M.R. James" rel="nofollow noopener">Oh, Whistle, and I'll Come to you, My Lad</a>, are included in most anthologies of the genre. <br /><br />Over the years, I have read quite a few of his, enjoying them immensely, before I finally bought this volume. Here I discovered more excellent tales but also so much more. The introduction to the author and his life was fascinating. I knew James was an academic but had no idea of his character. <br />Those details built a better image of how this repressed Victorian ended up penning such stories. Somehow, his fears and obsessions, combined with the settings he knew best, that of universities and visited locales, work amazingly well. Several themes do recur too, such as the danger of searching for truths. How contradictory that a scholar would be so afraid of ‘knowledge’? Actually, no, it makes sense if you take knowledge in the biblical sense... (now, I’m thinking of Philip Pullman. The way the mind jumps!). The volume also had an enlightening appendix of the author’s own writings on the genre. Again, this added a new angle. <br /><br />Favourite stories? Quite a few. ‘Oh Whistle’ of course, but also ‘Casting the Runes’, ‘Warning to the Curious’, ’The Tractate Middoth’,and ’Number 13’.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17383569762415732172" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


