<span id="freeTextContainer7332668640445841048">A timeless collection of England’s greatest ever ghost story writer - MR James.<br/>Often read at Christmas but great to read at anytime of the year, this collection of short often very unsettling ghost stories are easy to read and digest quickly but leave an indelible impression in your mind and imagination.<br/>There are too many to mention here but my three personal favourites are The Ash Tree, The Tractate Middoth and one of MR James most famous ghost stories, Oh Whistle and I’ll come to you my Lad.<br/>Cl</span>
  <span id="freeText7332668640445841048" style="display:none">A timeless collection of England’s greatest ever ghost story writer - MR James.<br />Often read at Christmas but great to read at anytime of the year, this collection of short often very unsettling ghost stories are easy to read and digest quickly but leave an indelible impression in your mind and imagination.<br />There are too many to mention here but my three personal favourites are The Ash Tree, The Tractate Middoth and one of MR James most famous ghost stories, Oh Whistle and I’ll come to you my Lad.<br />Classic, old but still as riveting and addictive as they must have been when first published, these are scary stories of classic ‘bump in the night’ phantoms and unsettling happenings which really stay with you long after finishing. Definitely a book to be read late at night with a candle lit and the windows, doors and curtains firmly closed.......</span>
